# u-boot environment access from Linux (fw_printenv / fw_setenv).
#
# u-boot stores its environment as the file "uboot.env" inside the FAT
# filesystem on the GPT partition named "env" (CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_FAT,
# CONFIG_ENV_FAT_DEVICE_AND_PART="0#env"). libubootenv cannot parse a
# FAT filesystem, so it accesses the environment through the mounted
# file: fstab mounts the "env" partition at /mnt/uboot-env.
#
# Format: <device>  <offset>  <env_size>
# A single line means a non-redundant environment, matching u-boot's
# FAT env (4-byte CRC + data, padded to CONFIG_ENV_SIZE = 0x10000).
/mnt/uboot-env/uboot.env  0x0000  0x10000
